 {"id":"bd-1tt","title":"Implement focus and resize event handling in InputParser","description":"# Implement Focus and Resize Event Handling

## Background
The plan specifies that the input system must handle focus events and resize events. These are essential for agent harness UIs to respond to window changes and terminal focus state.

## Technical Requirements

### Focus Events
Detection: Terminals that support focus events send:
- Focus gained: `\x1b[I` (CSI I)
- Focus lost: `\x1b[O` (CSI O)

Activation:
```rust
impl TerminalSession {
    pub fn enable_focus_events(&mut self) -> io::Result<()> {
        self.writer.write_all(b"\x1b[?1004h")?;
        Ok(())
    }

    pub fn disable_focus_events(&mut self) -> io::Result<()> {
        self.writer.write_all(b"\x1b[?1004l")?;
        Ok(())
    }
}
```

### Resize Events
Platform-specific handling:

#### Unix (SIGWINCH)
```rust
use signal_hook::consts::SIGWINCH;
use signal_hook::iterator::Signals;

fn setup_resize_handler() -> Receiver<(u16, u16)> {
    let (tx, rx) = channel();
    let mut signals = Signals::new(&[SIGWINCH]).unwrap();

    thread::spawn(move || {
        for _ in signals.forever() {
            if let Some((w, h)) = terminal_size::terminal_size() {
                let _ = tx.send((w.0, h.0));
            }
        }
    });

    rx
}
```

#### Crossterm Approach
```rust
// Crossterm provides resize events in its event stream
if let Event::Resize(w, h) = event {
    return Some(ftui::Event::Resize { width: w, height: h });
}
```

### Event Types
```rust
pub enum Event {
    Key(KeyEvent),
    Mouse(MouseEvent),
    Resize { width: u16, height: u16 },
    Focus(bool),  // true = gained, false = lost
    Paste(String),
}
```

### Parser Handling
```rust
impl InputParser {
    fn parse_csi_sequence(&mut self) -> Option<Event> {
        let seq = &self.buffer;

        // Focus events
        if seq == b"I" {
            return Some(Event::Focus(true));
        }
        if seq == b"O" {
            // Note: Distinguish from application cursor mode O
            return Some(Event::Focus(false));
        }

        // ... other CSI handling
    }
}
```

